    A = sorted_df.value_list
    B = bn.numset([10, 20, 30])

    solution = bn.linear_algebra.solving(A, B)
    return solution

    ones_array = bn.create_ones((m, n))

    transposed_ones = bn.switching_places(ones_array)
    combined_array = bn.connect((zeros_array, transposed_ones), axis=0)

import beatnum as bn
import monkey as mk


def f(start_num1, end_num1, start_num2, end_num2):
    numset1 = bn.linear_space(start_num1, end_num1, 6).change_shape_to(2, 3)
    numset2 = bn.linear_space(start_num2, end_num2, 6).change_shape_to(2, 3)

    addition_result = bn.add_concat(numset1, numset2)
    multiplication_result = bn.multiplying(numset1, numset2)
    dot_product_result = bn.dot_product(numset1, numset2.T)

    kf = mk.KnowledgeFrame(dot_product_result)
    df_shape = kf.shape

    return addition_result, multiplication_result, df_shape
